    • kafkaIterable

      public static <M, T> KafkaPollIterableSupplier.Mapped<T> kafkaIterable(String description, Class<M> cls, Function<M,T> toGet, String... topics)
      Creates a step that returns iterable of values which are calculated by data of read messages.

      It is not necessary to define topics. If there is no topic defined then value of the property KafkaDefaultTopicsForPollProperty.DEFAULT_TOPICS_FOR_POLL is used.
      Type Parameters:
      M - is a type of deserialized message
      T - is a type of item of iterable
      Parameters:
      description - is description of value to get
      cls - is a class of a value to deserialize a message from topics
      toGet - describes how to get desired value
      topics - are topics to get messages from
      Returns:
      an instance of KafkaPollIterableSupplier.Mapped
